03/05/2005
SKOPJE, Macedonia -- Mayor Trifun Kostovski announced on Monday (2 May) that Skopje would soon become a bilingual city, incorporating the use of Albanian as envisioned in the constitution. Kostovski cited several concrete measures to expand the use of Albanian and other languages in the local assembly and in his cabinet. He added that all official municipality documents would be published both in Macedonian and Albanian. Street signs will be written in the languages of all ethnicities that surpass the 20 per cent threshold in specific municipalities. (A1 TV - 02/05/05)
